I was just assuming the zyroth's example was in Java, since that is what the article's author favored. Not sure where you guys got the idea that it was C.<p>But, just to cover all bases, it wouldn't work as Java either. This would though.<p><pre><code>  int[] x = {1, 2, 3};
  for (int i = 0; i < 3; i++) { x[i] *= 2; }
</code></pre>
Yet another reason to use:<p><pre><code>  (mapcar #'(lambda (x) (* x 2)) '(1 2 3))
</code></pre>
... you don't have to think about whether array indexes start at zero or one.
